comments.body:
I'm seeing timeouts on s3$ls() for example, though this also impacts most other operations.  (I'm testing against a Redhat CEPH system which speaks the S3 API, not against master Amazon itself, which no doubt explains the greater latencies here... this probably is never an issue if I stuck with the commercial giant but just trying to test the open source options....)

I've found that setting the env var,
{code:java}
Sys.setenv(CURLOPT_ACCEPTTIMEOUT_MS=50000) {code}
seems to work though (I think), so maybe we'll all good...
